# Outside Inn Radio — VPS Reference

> How the 24/7 lo-fi radio works. Every command, every gotcha, everything you need to operate it.

---

## What It Is

A DigitalOcean VPS loops a pre-rendered video file (HoldtLoop.mp4) via FFmpeg and pushes it to Restream via RTMP. Restream forwards to YouTube. The VPS runs independently of your laptop — it stays on while you sleep, travel, or shut down.

```
VPS (FFmpeg) → Restream → YouTube
```

The video is stream-copied (no re-encoding), so CPU usage is near zero. A $6/month server handles it.

